### 16. He who leads a Town astray.

<span class="margnote">**M**.</span>VII. 10*b*. The one who leads a town
astray <span id="fr_337"></span>[3](#fn_333.md) is he who says outright,
"Let us go and worship idols."

**T**. XI. 5 *b*. R. Shimeon the son of Jehuda said in the name of R.
Shimeon, "He who leads a town astray is to die by strangulation," <span
id="fr_338"></span>[4](#fn_334.md)

------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Footnotes

<span id="fn_333"></span>[106:3](tsa28.htm#fr_337.md) Deut. 13. 12 ff.
Verse 16 orders that all those who are led astray are to he put to the
sword; cf. *Mishnah*. X. 7. But since in the case of the *mesith*, "the
beguiler" (Deut. 13. 6), who is expressly condemned to be stoned, the
word *l’haddiḥ’ka*, "to lead thee astray," is used, stoning must apply
to him also, on the principle of *gezera shawa;* *i.e.* the misleader is
to be stoned, and the misled decapitated.

<span id="fn_334"></span>[106:4](tsa28.htm#fr_338.md) R. Shimeon places
such a man in the category of the false prophet, *Mishnah* XI. 5.

